{{日本の法令 |題名=温泉法 |提出区分=閣法 |効力=現行法 |種類={{ill|Environmental law|ja|環境法|qq=draft}} |内容=温泉の保護、採取に伴う災害の防止および利用 |関連={{ill|Nature Conservation Law|ja|自然環境保全法|qq=draft}} |リンク={{Egov law}} |ウィキソース=温泉法 }}
'''Onsen Law''' (温泉法, 昭和23rd year 法律第125号) is a law in Japan concerning the protection of {{ill|onsen|ja|温泉|1=Onsen|1=Onsen|qq=draft}}.
== Purpose == This law aims to protect hot springs, prevent disasters caused by the extraction of combustible {{ill|natural gas|ja|天然ガス|qq=draft}}, and ensure the proper utilization of hot springs, thereby contributing to the enhancement of {{ill|public welfare|ja|公共の福祉|qq=draft}} (Article 1).
== Content == The law stipulates regulations for land excavation to extract hot springs, permissions for hot spring extraction, appropriate utilization, and display of {{ill|hot spring analysis report|ja|温泉分析書|1=Hot spring analysis report|qq=draft}} details.
Recent amendments address the {{ill|Onsen fraud issue|ja|温泉偽装問題|1=Onsen Fraud Controversy|qq=Onsen Fraud Scandal|qq=draft}} by mandating hot spring operators to submit an updated hot spring analysis report every 10 years as prescribed by the Onsen Law Enforcement Order. Following the {{ill|Shibuya Onsen Facility Explosion Incident|ja|渋谷温泉施設爆発事故|qq=draft}}, stricter guidelines were introduced for land excavation permissions and hot spring extraction permits to prevent disasters caused by combustible natural gas.
== Definition of Onsen == According to Article 2, Paragraph 1, onsen refers to hot water, mineral water, or gases (excluding natural gases primarily composed of hydrocarbons) that meet one of the following criteria:
# Water temperature at the source is 25°C or higher. (Water below 25°C may be referred to as {{ill|cold springs|ja|冷泉|qq=draft}} or {{ill|mineral springs|ja|鉱泉|1=Mineral spring|qq=draft}}.) # Contains at least one of the following substances in the specified minimum quantities per kilogram: {|class=wikitable style="font-size:small" ! Substance !! Minimum content per kg |- | Dissolved solids (excluding gases) || style="text-align:right"| 1,000 mg |- | Free {{ill|carbon dioxide|ja|炭酸|qq=draft}} (CO<sub>2</sub>) || style="text-align:right"| 250 mg |- | {{ill|Lithium ion|ja|リチウム|qq=draft}} (Li<sup>+</sup>) || style="text-align:right"| 1 mg |- | {{ill|Strontium ion|ja|ストロンチウム|qq=draft}} (Sr<sup>++</sup>) || style="text-align:right"| 10 mg |- | {{ill|Barium ion|ja|バリウム|qq=draft}} (Ba<sup>++</sup>) || style="text-align:right"| 5 mg |- | {{ill|Iron ions|ja|鉄|qq=draft}} (Fe<sup>++</sup>, Fe<sup>+++</sup>) || style="text-align:right"| 10 mg |- | Manganese ion (Mn<sup>++</sup>) || style="text-align:right"| 10 mg |- | {{ill|Hydrogen ion|ja|水素|qq=draft}} (H<sup>+</sup>) || style="text-align:right"| 1 mg |- | {{ill|Bromine ion|ja|臭素|qq=draft}} (Br<sup>-</sup>) || style="text-align:right"| 5 mg |- | {{ill|Iodine ion|ja|沃素|qq=draft}} (I<sup>-</sup>) || style="text-align:right"| 1 mg |- | {{ill|Fluoride ion|ja|フッ素|qq=draft}} (F<sup>-</sup>) || style="text-align:right"| 2 mg |- | Hydrogen arsenate ion (HAsO<sub>4</sub><sup>--</sup>) || style="text-align:right"| 1.3 mg |- | Metarsenous acid (HAsO<sub>2</sub>) || style="text-align:right"| 1 mg |- | Total {{ill|sulfur|ja|硫黄|qq=draft}} (S) [HS<sup>-</sup>, S<sub>2</sub>O<sub>3</sub><sup>--</sup>, H<sub>2</sub>S] || style="text-align:right"| 1 mg |- | {{ill|Metaboric acid|ja|ホウ酸|qq=draft}} (HBO<sub>2</sub>) || style="text-align:right"| 5 mg |- | {{ill|Metasilicic acid|ja|ケイ酸|qq=draft}} (H<sub>2</sub>SiO<sub>3</sub>) || style="text-align:right"| 50 mg |- | Sodium bicarbonate (NaHCO<sub>3</sub>) || style="text-align:right"| 340 mg |- | {{ill|Radon|ja|ラドン|qq=draft}} (Rn) || style="text-align:right"| 20×10<sup>-10</sup> Ci |- | {{ill|Radium salts|ja|ラジウム|qq=draft}} (as Ra) || style="text-align:right"| 1×10<sup>-8</sup> mg |}
== Structure == * Chapter 1: General Provisions (Articles 1-2) * Chapter 2: Protection of Onsen (Articles 3-14) * Chapter 3: Prevention of Disasters Related to Onsen Extraction (Articles 14-2 to 14-10) * Chapter 4: Utilization of Onsen (Articles 15-31) * Chapter 5: Advisory and Hearings (Articles 32-33) * Chapter 6: Miscellaneous Provisions (Articles 34-37) * Chapter 7: Penal Provisions (Articles 38-43) * Supplementary Provisions == See Also == * {{ill|Hot spring analysis report|ja|温泉分析書|1=Hot spring analysis report|qq=draft}} * {{ill|Mineral Spring Analysis Guidelines|ja|鉱泉分析法指針|1=Guidelines for Mineral Spring Analysis|qq=draft}} * {{ill|Onsen fraud issue|ja|温泉偽装問題|1=Onsen Fraud Controversy|qq=Onsen Fraud Scandal|qq=draft}} * {{ill|Bathing tax|ja|入湯税|qq=draft}}
== External Links == * [https://www.env.go.jp/nature/onsen/index.html Protection and Utilization of Onsen] - Ministry of the Environment * [https://www.env.go.jp/nature/onsen/docs/pamph_aramashi.html Overview of Onsen Law Revisions] - Ministry of the Environment * [https://laws.e-gov.go.jp/document?lawid=323AC0000000125&openerCode=1 Onsen Law] - {{ill|e-Gov Law Search|ja|e-Gov法令検索|qq=draft}}
